==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Contorniate
<hw>Con*tor"ni*a`te</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos>,
<ety>[It. <ets>contorniato</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>contorniare</ets> to
make a circuit or outline, fr. <ets>contorno</ets> circuit, outline. See
<er>Contour</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Numis.)</fld> <def>A species of medal or
medallion of bronze, having a deep furrow on the contour or edge; --
supposed to have been struck in the days of <person>Constantine</person>
and his successors.</def> <rj><au>R. S. Poole.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contorsion</ent>⟦br⟧
